title: Highest and Lowest Average Humidity, USA, 2007
name: Highest and Lowest Average Humidity, USA, 2007
description: This dataset illustrates the highest and lowest average humidity in cities with 50,000 people or more.  A value of -1 means that no data was applicable.  Also shown are the city housing population, the percent of humidity, the name of the city and state, the rankings both high and low, and the inverse rankings to be used for mapping only.Source:  City-DataURL:  http://www.city-data.com/top2/c485.htmlhttp://www.city-data.com/top2/c486.htmlDate Accessed: November 13, 2007
